    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.36"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE COLLEGE OF WOOSTER 
                        <lb/>
                    WOOSTER, OHIO</hi> 44691
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 30, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska, 68505</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This is simply a note of thanks for granting me <del>to</del><add>the</add> use <add>of</add> the two stanzas from <hi rend="underline">The Poet's Town</hi> in my book. I appreciate it very much.</p>
                
                <p>Mrs. Young was kind enough to enclose with the permission this list of your works and the program of the ceremonies at the Nebraska Capitol in April of this year. I cannot claim to have read all the works on the list, but I remember with a great deal of pleasure reading a good part of The Cycle of the West some years ago, and never forgetting some lines (I think from the Song of Hugh Glass)</p>
                
                <lg>
                    <l>Alas, the journey back <del>y</del><add>t</add>o yesterwhiles</l> 
                    <l>How tangled are the trails, thw<sic>the</sic> <del>e</del><add>w</add>eary miles</l> 
                    <l>How stubbornly they stretch, and if one win</l> 
                    <l>The long <del>e</del><add>w</add>ay back in search of what has been</l> 
                    <l>Shall he find aught that is not strange and new<add><unclear>?</unclear></add></l> 
                </lg>
                
                <p>The books gave me real enjoyment, and I can only add my thanks for all that to you along with my specific gratitude for the use of the quotation.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute> 
                    
                    <signed>Melcher P. Fobes</signed> 
                    <signed>Mel<del/><add>c</add>her P. Fobes</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw>1</fw> 
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
